<p>The Trustees of the Irish Permanent Pension Plan have provided this site to keep you apprised of developments in relation to the winding up of the pension plan.  This site will provide you with general information together with details of your individual entitlements.</p>

<p>(The Trustees of the plan are Irish Pensions Trust Limited, Sean O’Keefe, Clive Lennon, Frank Singleton, Gavin Long and Alan Broxson.)</p>

<h2>How to navigate the website</h2>

<strong>About the Plan</strong>
<p>This page provides you with the background to the winding up of the plan, together with an overview of the process the Trustees will follow.</p>

<strong>Confirm your Personal Details</strong>
<p>The Trustees invite you to verify the details held on the plan records in your respect.  You should take the time to ensure this information is correct as it will have a direct impact on the benefits payable to you.</p>

<strong>Your Options</strong>
<p>Once the calculations have been completed by the plan actuary, this page will update and contain details of your individual entitlement and the options associated with your entitlements.</p>

<strong>FAQ’s</strong>
<p>This section contains the most frequently asked questions and answers.</p>

<strong>Contact Us</strong>
<p>You are invited to contact Allied Pension Trustees Limited (APT), the wind up administrator with any questions you may have.</p>

